data <- read_excel(tf)

Filter the countries.

data_f <- data %>%
  filter(country == "United Kingdom" | country == "Australia" | country == "United States")

Clean the column name.

names(data_f) <- make.names(names(data_f))

Lets see how life ladder changes through time.

ggplot(data_f, aes(x = Life.Ladder, y = year, group = country, colour = country)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  coord_flip() +
  transition_reveal(year)

Lets check the relationship between GDP per capita and life ladder.

ggplot(data_f, aes(x = Log.GDP.per.capita, y = Life.Ladder, colour = country)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm") +
  facet_wrap("country", scales = "free")
